    "annotations": [
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "FUNCTION",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Component of the ERMES/MDM complex, which serves as a molecular tether to connect the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) and mitochondria. Components of this complex are involved in the control of mitochondrial shape and protein biogenesis, and function in nonvesicular lipid trafficking between the ER and mitochondria. The MDM12-@GENE_NAME@ subcomplex functions in the major beta-barrel assembly pathway that is responsible for biogenesis of all outer membrane beta-barrel proteins, and acts in a late step after the SAM complex. The MDM10-MDM12-@GENE_NAME@ subcomplex further acts in the TOM40-specific pathway after the action of the MDM12-@GENE_NAME@ complex. Essential for establishing and maintaining the structure of mitochondria and maintenance of mtDNA nucleoids"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SUBCELLULAR LOCATION",
          "subcellularLocations": [
            {
              "location": {
                "value": "Endoplasmic reticulum membrane"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SIMILARITY",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Belongs to the MMM1 family"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SUBUNIT",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Homodimer. Component of the ER-mitochondria encounter structure (ERMES) or MDM complex, composed of @GENE_NAME@, MDM10, MDM12 and MDM34. A @GENE_NAME@ homodimer associates with one molecule of MDM12 on each side in a pairwise head-to-tail manner, and the SMP-LTD domains of @GENE_NAME@ and MDM12 generate a continuous hydrophobic tunnel for phospholipid trafficking"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
